parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Booster and Brake Booster Pump Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster and brake booster pump assembly can cause the loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes do not engage properly
and traction control lights illuminate on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience a longer braking distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator/booster can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and a warning light with a circle around it are on
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid propulsion system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Check hybrid system warning light is on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inverter can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Check hybrid system warning light is on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various warning lights to illuminate, making it difficult or impossible to diagnose the problem, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the headlights can reduce visibility, making it difficult or impossible to drive safely, which can lead to accidents.
